Afterward, he said, “As a Black man, I took over a neo-Nazi group and outsmarted them,” and that he intends to dismantle the group from within.
All of this may finally signal a change in how Portland law enforcement treats the far right.
The far right loves to use violence — but it can only do this if law enforcement permits.
All of these separate parts of the far right flourished as they egged on and aided each other, united by their support of Trump.
They have become influential on the Atomwaffen Division, a U.S. neo-Nazi group whose affiliates killed five people in 2017 and 2018.